  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educating communities at risk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOC coordinates four regional tsunami warning systems in Pacific, Indian Ocean, Caribbean and NE Atlantic, Mediterranean and connected seas. An effective tsunami early warning system is achieved when all persons, especially in vulnerable coastal communities are prepared and respond appropriately to Tsunami alerts. This element support sustainable and long-term Regional Tsunami Information Centers. TICs work in tandem with the regional warning systems, build on and strengthen national and regional institutional arrangements for disaster risk reduction through i.e tsunami information materials, best-practice, training courses, cross-learning activities in disaster risk reduction, and community-based programs. They pilot regional community based tsunami preparedness recognition programs.</narrative>
  </description>
